review_data: Reviewed in the United States on September 17, 2021
name: Emma
title: Tasted okay, still spiked blood sugar
review: I have type 1 diabetes and I'd been looking for a cereal that satisfied my craving for something crunchy and sweet, and Catalina Crunch fit the bill pretty well. Tastes okay, obviously not like real cereal and it has a strong sugar-substitute taste, but I don't mind it. HOWEVER it's interesting to me that this is marketed as being keto but I still need to use insulin for it - without it, my blood sugar would still rise significantly, so I'd be interested to see how people on a keto or low-carb diet are affected by it.
